The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, July 09, 2004 				 More for PMO 
New Delhi, July 8: Conventional wisdom has it people do not value free advice. So the National Advisory Councils views will come at a cost to the taxpayer.																								The NCA, led by Sonia Gandhi, has pushed up the budgetary requirements of the Prime Ministers Office, which has already been allotted 2 Motilal Nehru Marg by the Centre to accommodate the council. The outlay for the PMO has gone up to Rs 14.39 crore from Rs 12.83 crore proposed in Jaswant Singhs interim budget. 
